div class=3D"md-sentinel--spy-target"></div><section data-level=3D"1" id=3D=
"ref1" data-has-spy=3D"true"><!--[PREMOD1]--><span class=3D"marker PREMOD1 =
mod-inline"></span><p class=3D"topic-paragraph"><strong><span id=3D"ref5116=
84"></span>war</strong>,  in the popular sense, a conflict between politica=
l groups involving hostilities of considerable <a class=3D"md-dictionary-li=
nk md-dictionary-tt-off eb" data-term=3D"duration" href=3D"https://www.brit=
annica.com/dictionary/duration" data-type=3D"EB">duration</a> and magnitude=
. In the usage of <a href=3D"https://www.britannica.com/topic/social-scienc=
e" class=3D"md-crosslink autoxref " data-show-preview=3D"true">social scien=
ce</a>, certain qualifications are added. <span id=3D"ref511685"></span><a =
href=3D"https://www.britannica.com/topic/sociology" class=3D"md-crosslink "=
 data-show-preview=3D"true">Sociologists</a> usually apply the term to such=
 conflicts only if they are initiated and conducted in accordance with soci=
ally recognized forms. They treat war as an institution recognized in custo=
m or in <a href=3D"https://www.britannica.com/topic/law" class=3D"md-crossl=
ink autoxref " data-show-preview=3D"true">law</a>. Military writers usually=
 confine the term to hostilities in which the contending groups are suffici=
ently equal in power to render the outcome uncertain for a time. Armed conf=
licts of powerful states with isolated and powerless peoples are usually ca=
lled pacifications, <a href=3D"https://www.britannica.com/topic/armed-force=
" class=3D"md-crosslink autoxref " data-show-preview=3D"true">military</a> =
expeditions, or explorations; with small states, they are called interventi=
ons or reprisals; and with internal groups, rebellions or <a class=3D"md-di=
ctionary-link md-dictionary-tt-off eb" data-term=3D"insurrections" href=3D"=
https://www.britannica.com/dictionary/insurrections" data-type=3D"EB">insur=
rections</a>. Such incidents, if the resistance is sufficiently strong or p=
rotracted, may achieve a magnitude that entitles them to the name =E2=80=9C=
war.=E2=80=9D</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_1_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad=
