span><!--[H3]--><span class=3D"marker h3"></span><div class=3D"md-sentinel-=
-spy-target"></div><section data-level=3D"1" id=3D"ref53511" data-has-spy=
=3D"true"><h1 class=3D"h1">The causes of war</h1><!--[TOC]--> <!--[PREMOD1]=
--><span class=3D"marker PREMOD1 mod-inline"></span><p class=3D"topic-parag=
raph">Contemporary theories of the causes of war divide roughly into two ma=
jor schools. One attributes war to certain innate biological and psychologi=
cal factors or drives, the other attributes it to certain social relations =
and institutions. Both schools include optimists and pessimists concerning =
the preventability of war.</p><!--[MOD1]--><span class=3D"marker MOD1 mod-i=
nline"></span> <div class=3D"md-sentinel--spy-target"></div><section data-l=
